# Environment Variables — darkTunes Charts

Copy this file to `.env.local` for local development.
All variables marked **required for production** must be set in Vercel project settings before going live.

```env
# =============================================================================
# SPOTIFY WEB API
# =============================================================================
# Register at: https://developer.spotify.com/dashboard
# Required for: /api/spotify — fetching real monthly listener counts for bands
# Without this, the API returns the seeded mock values from seedData.ts
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID=your_spotify_client_id_here
SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET=your_spotify_client_secret_here

# =============================================================================
# EXCHANGE RATE API (optional)
# =============================================================================
# Register at: https://www.exchangerate-api.com/ (free tier: 1500 req/month)
# Required for: Displaying tier prices in local currencies (EUR is the default)
# If unset, all prices are shown in EUR only
EXCHANGE_RATE_API_KEY=your_exchange_rate_api_key_here

# =============================================================================
# VERCEL KV (optional — replaces in-memory store for multi-instance production)
# =============================================================================
# Provided automatically by Vercel when you add the KV storage integration
# Required for: persistent data across cold-start serverless instances
# Without this, each cold start resets the in-memory store to seed data
# KV_REST_API_URL=https://your-kv.upstash.io
# KV_REST_API_TOKEN=your_kv_token_here

# =============================================================================
# DEVELOPMENT ONLY
# =============================================================================
# Node environment — set automatically by Vite / Vercel
# NODE_ENV=development
```

## Variable Reference

| Variable | Required | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID` | Production | — | Spotify Web API client ID |
| `SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET` | Production | — | Spotify Web API client secret |
| `EXCHANGE_RATE_API_KEY` | Optional | — | Exchange rate conversion API key |
| `KV_REST_API_URL` | Optional | — | Vercel KV Redis endpoint |
| `KV_REST_API_TOKEN` | Optional | — | Vercel KV authentication token |

## Setup Guide

### Spotify API Credentials

1. Go to [Spotify Developer Dashboard](https://developer.spotify.com/dashboard)
2. Click **Create App**
3. Fill in App name: `darkTunes Charts`, App description: `Music chart platform`
4. Add Redirect URI: `https://your-vercel-domain.vercel.app/callback`
5. Copy **Client ID** and **Client Secret** into your environment

### Vercel Configuration

```bash
# Via Vercel CLI
vercel env add SPOTIFY_CLIENT_ID
vercel env add SPOTIFY_CLIENT_SECRET

# Or in Vercel Dashboard → Project → Settings → Environment Variables
```
